Sentence: Recently, superconductivity with transition temperature (T c ) up to 10 K has been discovered in novel BiS -based layered compounds, with chemical formulas of Bi O 4 S 3 , REO âx 1 F x BiS 2 (RE: La , Ce , , Pr , and Yb ), and La âx 1 M x OBiS 2 (M = Ti, Zr, Hf, Th) .
Similarly, a recent examination of Bi 4 O 4 S 3 superconductors revealed at least two phases in the Bi-O-S compound: Bi 2 OS 2 and Bi 3 O 2 S 3 .
The optimal F-doping concentration is about 0.24 in BiO âx 1 F x BiS 2 , where the highest transition temperature of 3.5 K is achieved.
The T c value is about 3.5 K for the x = 0.24 sample, which is defined as the onset of the superconducting transition.
The T c value decreases to about 2.7 K for the x = 0.27 sample.
